gures of Mexican letters for his scholarship and criticism, and careful readers will recognize a scholar's attention to accuracy within the novel's dyspeptic descriptions of Mexico City. The places described are indeed real (this edition includes a map that marks those visited in the story), though a few have since closed or been put to new uses. Dick Gerdes's elegant translation now preserves them all for a new audience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aCollege teacherszMexicozMexico CityvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aGallo, Rubén, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGallo, Rubén.1 aGerdes, Dick.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292793576423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292793576/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK